<h1>Pickled Red Onions</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 small red onion, thinly sliced</li>
<li>2/3 cups white vinegar</li>
<li>2/3 cups water</li>
<li>5 teaspoons sugar</li>
<li>2 teaspoons salt</li>
<li>1 garlic clove</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Place the red onion in a 1-pint mason jar.</li>
<li>Heat the white vingar, water, sugar, and salt in a medium saucepan over medium heat.</li>
<li>Stir until the sugar and salt dissolve, then remove from heat.</li>
<li>Let mixture cool enough to touch.</li>
<li>Pour mixture into the mason jar.</li>
<li>Once cooled to room temperature, store jar in fridge.</li>
<li>Onions are ready to eat once bright pink and tender (1 hour for very thinly sliced onions).</li>
</ol>
